    {
      "id": "/page/1/TextInlineMath/3",
      "block_type": "TextInlineMath",
      "html": "<p block-type=\"TextInlineMath\">In a seminal paper on the subject, Grossman and Zhou [15] show how to extend the Merton framework to encompass a more general drawdown constraint of <i>Wt</i> ≥ <i>αMt</i> , where <i>Wt</i> is the wealth level at time <i>t,Mt</i> is the running maximum wealth up to that point, that is, <i>Mt</i> = max0<sup>≤</sup><i>u</i>≤<i><sup>t</sup></i> <i>Wu</i>, and <i>α</i> is an exogenous number between 0 and 1.</p>",
      "page": 354,
      "polygon": [
        [
          78.697265625,
          141.7275390625
        ],
        [
          289.3515625,
          141.7275390625
        ],
        [
          289.3515625,
          220.0810546875
        ],
