      },
      "images": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "/page/1/Text/4",
      "block_type": "Text",
      "html": "<p block-type=\"Text\">The motivation for this constraint is that, in practice, a fund manager may implicitly be subject to redemptions that depend on whether the manager's portfolio stays above a (possibly discounted) previous high, <i>Mt</i> .</p>",
      "page": 354,
      "polygon": [
        [
          78.841796875,
          221.634765625
